<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1215,1401]" box="[264,402,1215,1240]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[264,402,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1215,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Female: body approximately 
<number box="[654,713,1255,1281]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2700.0">2700</number>
long, body colour red. Ocular plate 
<number box="[1134,1178,1255,1281]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="421.0">421</number>
long. Capitulum 
<number box="[335,379,1295,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="413.0">413</number>
long. Genital field with two rows of 
<number box="[843,872,1295,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="10.0">10</number>
setae. Number of acetabula approximately 
<number box="[355,388,1335,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="80.0">80</number>
. Lengths of PI–PV: 
<number box="[641,722,1335,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="12.62">12, 62</number>
, 
<number box="[738,818,1335,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="50.68">50, 68</number>
, 
<number box="[835,868,1335,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="22.0">22</number>
. Lengths of I­leg­ 
<number box="[1095,1134,1335,1361]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4­6</number>
: 116, 150, 140. Lengths of IV­leg­ 
<number box="[488,524,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4­6</number>
: 266, 288, 246. For all other characters see 
<bibRefCitation author="Harvey" box="[1035,1210,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" refString="Harvey, M. S. (1990) A review of the water mite family Limnocharidae in Australia (Acarina). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 3, 483 - 493." type="journal article" year="1990">
Harvey (
<number box="[1137,1201,1375,1401]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1455,1881]" box="[264,366,1455,1480]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis box="[264,366,1455,1480]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1455,1881]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Adults of 
<taxonomicName box="[433,712,1495,1520]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnocharidae" genus="Limnochares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australica">
<emphasis box="[433,712,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Limnochares australica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are virtually indistinguishable from the Indian and African specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike. However, Martin &amp; Smit (2002)" authorityName="Koenike. However, Martin &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2002" box="[522,1131,1535,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnocharidae" genus="Limnochares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinita">
<emphasis box="[522,631,1535,1560]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">L. crinita</emphasis>
Koenike. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[873,1131,1535,1561]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" refString="Martin, P. &amp; Smit, H. (2002) The larval morphology and host of the Australian water mite Limnochares australica (Acari: Hydrachnidia: Limnocharidae). Records of the Western Australian Museum, 20, 409 - 414." type="journal article" year="2002">
Martin &amp; Smit (
<number box="[1062,1124,1535,1561]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
showed that the larvae of both species were quite different. Outside 
<collectingCountry box="[931,1041,1575,1601]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Australia</collectingCountry>
, the species has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[433,590,1615,1641]" name="New Zealand" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smit" box="[606,730,1615,1641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" refString="Smit, H. (1996) New species of water mites from New Zealand, with remarks on the water mites from ponds and lakes (Acari, Hydrachnellae). Acarologia, 37, 45 - 53." type="journal article" year="1996">
Smit 
<number box="[670,730,1615,1641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[796,977,1615,1641]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(Smit 
<number box="[1057,1120,1615,1641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2002.0">2002</number>
), so it is reported here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[595,640,1655,1681]" name="Fiji" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fiji</collectingCountry>
. All these specimens were tentatively assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Limnocharidae" genus="Limnochares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">L. australica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as larvae were unknown. The same applies to the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1148,1192,1695,1721]" name="Fiji" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, and therefore the assignment to 
<taxonomicName box="[540,692,1735,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnocharidae" genus="Limnochares" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australica">
<emphasis box="[540,692,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">L. australica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be considered as tentative. Leg segments from specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[459,641,1775,1801]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[699,740,1775,1801]" name="Fiji" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fiji</collectingCountry>
are shorter than those given for Australian specimens by 
<bibRefCitation author="Harvey" box="[379,558,1815,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="20" refString="Harvey, M. S. (1990) A review of the water mite family Limnocharidae in Australia (Acarina). Invertebrate Taxonomy, 3, 483 - 493." type="journal article" year="1990">
Harvey (
<number box="[486,549,1815,1841]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, but there is a considerable variation in the morphology, both between and within populations.
</paragraph>
